<dl id="n05033j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05033j">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05033j"> 33(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Copyist (mind, eye &amp; hand)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The younger monks spent much of their time in copying books, &lsquo;a labour,&rsquo; says an old writer, &lsquo;that occupies the mind with the sense of the words, the eyes with reading them, the hand with writing them.&rsquo; <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 44</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
